jobs.name: Multiple Hash Keys
jobs.description: This transformation job can take up to two tables. If you need to add more tables you have to modify the initial join. After this, the job creates the HASH KEY using the Natural Key defined in the Grid Variables, creates constant variables such as the record_source and the load_datetime and at the end creates a view to be used in the following jobs to create the Hubs and Satellites.

jobs.name: Single Hash key
jobs.description: This transformation job takes only one source table. You only have to add what is required in the Grid Variables. Then creates the hashing for the business key, constant value and a view to use in the following steps.

select ABBR, TITLE, INTERNAL_ID, NAME,
HK_CENTER_ID as DIM_CENTER_HK,
HASHDIFF,load_datetime,record_source,ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY dim_center_hk ORDER BY LOAD_DATETIME DESC) as ROW_NUM
FROM edw.raw_vault.SAT_CENTER
QUALIFY row_num = 1

WITH cte_LAST_RECORD AS(

    select  a.*,
    HK_DEPARTMENT_ID as DIM_DEPARTMENT_HK,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY dim_department_hk ORDER BY LOAD_DATETIME DESC) as ROW_NUM
    FROM EDW.RAW_VAULT.SAT_DEPARTMENT a
    QUALIFY row_num = 1
    
), cte_RETURN AS (
    SELECT COUNT(SPECIALTY) AS COUNT_SPECIALTY, DEPARTMENT_NAME
    FROM cte_LAST_RECORD
    GROUP BY DEPARTMENT_NAME
)

SELECT * FROM cte_RETURN ORDER BY 1

WITH cte_LAST_RECORD AS(
    SELECT enc.*,
    enc.HK_ENCOUNTER_ID AS DIM_ENCOUNTER_HK,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY dim_encounter_hk ORDER BY LOAD_DATETIME DESC) as ROW_NUM
    FROM edw.raw_vault.SAT_ENCOUNTER enc
    QUALIFY row_num = 1
),
cte_POSITION_MEASURE AS(
    SELECT MIN(WEIGHT) AS MIN_WEIGHT,
    AVG(WEIGHT) AS AVERAGE_WEIGHT,
    MAX(WEIGHT) AS MAX_WEIGHT,
    MIN(TEMPERATURE) AS MIN_TEMP,
    AVG(TEMPERATURE) AS AVERAGE_TEMP,
    MAX(TEMPERATURE) AS MAX_TEMP,
    MIN(RESPIRATIONS) AS MIN_RESPIRATIONS,
    AVG(RESPIRATIONS) AS AVERAGE_RESPIRATIONS,
    MAX(RESPIRATIONS) AS MAX_RESPIRATIONS,
    DEPARTMENT_ID
FROM
    cte_LAST_RECORD
GROUP BY
    DEPARTMENT_ID
)

SELECT * FROM cte_POSITION_MEASURE ORDER BY 1
